This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the vulnerability of neural networks and improving their robustness through adversarial training. It also involves experiments on image datasets, which are commonly used in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper discusses the sensitivity of neural networks to input transformations and the robustness of human vision to such transformations. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with improving the performance of neural networks through adversarial training, which is a common technique in AI research. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the vulnerability of neural networks to adversarial attacks and improving their robustness against such attacks. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with neural networks and their vulnerability to adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the field of neural computing.
